exports[`Phase 1 exit proof — real lexicon (T-043 / T-044) > snapshot: the Rikta/Krishna base reading is stable and distinct 1`] = `
"## The Day-Lord

Ravivara (Sunday) — the day of the Sun. The day burns with the steady radiance of the self, and the soul warms toward its own centre. selfhood, vitality, and the radiant center You might notice a quiet pull toward whatever feels most essential and true in you.

## The Lunar Day

Chaturthi (Krishna) — a Rikta lunar day of the waning fortnight, the gibbous arc narrowing, held by Ganesha. A deep clearing opens, dissolving obstacles from within. There may be a deep inner clearing, something dissolving from within.

## The Moon's Mansion

The Moon rests in Purva Bhadrapada, ruled by Jupiter, its symbol A sword, the front legs of a funeral cot (Manushya (human)). A fervent, two-sided fire burns toward radical transformation. You might notice an intensity that reaches past the ordinary, and a spark of the visionary.

## Conditions of the Day

The yoga is Atiganda (An inauspicious yoga; the name means "great danger" or "great knot," traditionally ascribed obstruction, friction, and hazard.); the karana is Balava (movable). A tightened knot sits somewhere in the grain of the day. A youthful, Brahma-blessed strength moves through the hours, buoyant and devotional. There may be a snag or two in the day's grain, meeting more resistance than usual.

---

The sky above is the same for everyone today. To see how this weather meets your own pattern, add your birth moment."
